          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron spectrum in the forward direction extends",
                " over the energy range of 11.5 - 43.5 MeV. The maximum",
                " intensity occurs at a neutron energy of about 22.5MeV",
                " and the FWHM of the spectrum is 15.8 MeV. Neutron flux",
                " densities were calculated from the integrated charge",
                " at the Be converter using Faraday cup.",
                " The neutron flux densities available at irradiation",
                " geometry were about 8.E+10 neutrons/cm**2/sec.",
                "  Neutron spectrum provided by S.M.Qaim ( 29-12-2016):",
                "  units: energy - MeV, yield - 10**8n/(muC*MeV*sr)",
                " Energy   Neutron yield       Energy   Neutron yield",
                "  12.5     124.                 29.5      140.",
                "  13.5     158.                 30.5      115.",
                "  14.5     175.                 31.5      102.",
                "  15.5     199.                 32.5       85.",
                "  16.5     196.                 33.5       76.",
                "  17.5     208.                 34.5       58.",
                "  18.5     232.                 35.5       56.",
                "  19.5     251.                 36.5       47.",
                "  20.5     260.                 37.5       46.",
                "  22.5     259.                 38.5       40.",
                "  23.5     246.                 39.5       34.",
                "  24.5     238.                 40.5       31.",
                "  25.5     219.                 41.5       27.",
                "  26.5     192.                 42.5       24.",
                "  27.5     172.                 43.5       21.",
                "  28.5     152."
              ]
            }
